    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-12-05T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-12-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="202"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d202">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Roosevelt Papers</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The President’s Chief of Staff</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_LFAWD1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Leahy</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">President</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-12-05">5 December
                        1944</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Admiral <persName corresp="#p_LFAWD1">Leahy</persName> to the President:</p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_SERJ1">Stettinius</persName> suggests that the following
                    be sent to Prime today: President to Prime.</p>
                <p>I have received from U. J. messages dated second and third December<note n="1"
                        xml:id="d202fn1">
                        <hi rend="italic">Supra</hi>.</note> regarding his talks with <persName
                        corresp="#p_DG1">de Gaulle</persName> and am informed he sent you identical
                    messages.</p>
                <p>I would like to have your views before I reply to <persName corresp="#p_S16"
                        >Stalin</persName>. <persName corresp="#p_RFD1">Roosevelt</persName>.<note
                        n="2" xml:id="d202fn2">A White House notation on the original reads: “Sent
                        to <gloss target="#t_PM1">PM</gloss> as No. 667.”</note>
                </p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
